{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PBrbL21DY7C1rJhs7N8Ggy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01A2Gdt9D7G87SRPGT1cSVFu","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n spark-pi create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'FINDINGS'\n============================================================\nSPARK-PI NAMESPACE — COMPLIANCE AUDIT REPORT\nDate: 2026-06-14\nAuditor: read-only inspection (no cluster changes made)\n============================================================\n\n=== COMPLIANT ITEMS ===\n\n[RBAC-OK-1] Dedicated ServiceAccount\n  A dedicated ServiceAccount 'spark-pi' is used by all three workloads\n  (spark-master Deployment, spark-worker Deployment, spark-pi Job). The\n  'default' ServiceAccount is not used by any workload.\n\n[RBAC-OK-2] Namespace-scoped Role (not ClusterRole)\n  Role 'spark-pi-role' is namespace-scoped, limiting blast radius if the\n  credentials are compromised. Verbs granted: create, get, list, watch,\n  delete, update, patch on resources: pods, services, configmaps,\n  persistentvolumeclaims.\n\n[RBAC-OK-3] RoleBinding correctly wired\n  RoleBinding 'spark-pi-role-binding' correctly binds 'spark-pi-role' to\n  the 'spark-pi' ServiceAccount within the spark-pi namespace.\n\n[IMG-OK-1] Pinned image tag (not 'latest')\n  All workloads use the same explicit version tag: apache/spark:3.5.3.\n  'latest' or floating tags are not used.\n\n[IMG-OK-2] Consistent imagePullPolicy\n  imagePullPolicy is set to 'IfNotPresent' on all three workloads, which\n  is consistent with the pinned tag and avoids redundant registry pulls.\n\n[RES-OK-1] Resource requests and limits set on all workloads\n  spark-master:  requests cpu=200m memory=512Mi / limits cpu=500m memory=1Gi\n  spark-worker:  requests cpu=200m memory=512Mi / limits cpu=500m memory=1Gi\n  spark-pi job:  requests cpu=200m memory=512Mi / limits cpu=500m memory=1Gi\n  All workloads have both requests and limits configured, preventing\n  unbounded resource consumption.\n\n[JOB-OK-1] Job configuration appropriate\n  The spark-pi Job has backoffLimit=0 (no retry on failure) and\n  restartPolicy=Never, which is correct for a batch compute job.\n  The Job completed successfully (1 succeeded pod).\n\n=== NON-COMPLIANT / GAPS ===\n\n[SEC-GAP-1] CRITICAL — Empty security context on all pods and containers\n  Pod-level securityContext is '{}' on spark-master, spark-worker, and\n  the spark-pi Job pod. No container-level securityContext is set either.\n  Missing security controls:\n    - runAsNonRoot: true  (containers may run as root/UID 0)\n    - runAsUser / runAsGroup  (no non-zero UID enforced)\n    - allowPrivilegeEscalation: false  (privilege escalation not blocked)\n    - readOnlyRootFilesystem: true  (root FS is writable)\n    - capabilities.drop: [ALL]  (no Linux capability dropping)\n    - seccompProfile  (no seccomp profile applied)\n  Remediation: add a pod-level and container-level securityContext with\n  the above fields to all three workload specs.\n\n[NET-GAP-1] HIGH — No NetworkPolicy defined\n  The spark-pi namespace has no NetworkPolicy resources. All pod-to-pod\n  and pod-to-external traffic is unrestricted. A compromised container\n  can reach any endpoint inside or outside the cluster.\n  Remediation: define ingress/egress NetworkPolicies that allow only the\n  necessary communication paths (e.g., worker→master on port 7077,\n  deny-all default).\n\n[IMG-GAP-1] HIGH — Image tag is mutable; no digest pinning\n  'apache/spark:3.5.3' is a mutable tag — the underlying image can be\n  replaced at the registry without changing the tag. An attacker who\n  compromises Docker Hub could serve a malicious image.\n  Remediation: pin images by digest, e.g.\n    apache/spark:3.5.3@sha256:<digest>\n  and verify the digest against a trusted source.\n\n[RBAC-GAP-1] MEDIUM — Role verbs broader than minimum required\n  The 'spark-pi-role' grants 'update' and 'patch' on pods, and 'delete'\n  on configmaps and persistentvolumeclaims. The Spark driver typically\n  only needs create/get/list/watch/delete on pods, and get/list/watch on\n  configmaps and services. Granting update/patch on pods and delete on\n  configmaps exceeds the minimum necessary privilege.\n  Remediation: review each verb against actual Spark driver API call\n  patterns and remove unnecessary verbs.\n\n[RBAC-GAP-2] MEDIUM — ServiceAccount token automounting not explicitly disabled\n  Neither the 'spark-pi' nor the 'default' ServiceAccount sets\n  'automountServiceAccountToken: false'. All pods automatically receive a\n  projected SA token volume (confirmed in pod specs). If a workload does\n  not need API server access, the token should not be mounted.\n  Remediation: set automountServiceAccountToken: false on the ServiceAccount\n  and re-enable per-pod only where genuinely needed.\n\n[NS-GAP-1] LOW — No LimitRange or ResourceQuota in namespace\n  No LimitRange or ResourceQuota is configured for the spark-pi namespace.\n  Without these, future workloads added to the namespace can run without\n  resource constraints (current workloads do set per-pod limits, but\n  enforcement is not namespace-policy-enforced).\n  Remediation: add a ResourceQuota to cap total namespace resource\n  consumption and a LimitRange to provide default limits for pods that\n  omit them.\n\n[IMG-GAP-2] LOW — Public registry without credential management\n  Images are pulled from Docker Hub (docker.io) without imagePullSecrets.\n  This relies on unauthenticated public pull access, which is subject to\n  Docker Hub rate limits and does not provide auditability of pulls.\n  Remediation: mirror the image to a private registry, configure\n  imagePullSecrets referencing those credentials.\n\n=== SUMMARY ===\n\n  Compliant: 7 items (RBAC structure, resource limits, image tag, job config)\n  Gaps:      7 items\n    Critical: 1 (missing security context on all workloads)\n    High:     2 (no NetworkPolicy, mutable image tag)\n    Medium:   2 (over-permissive RBAC verbs, SA token automounting)\n    Low:      2 (no LimitRange/ResourceQuota, no private registry)\n\nNo changes were made to the cluster during this audit.\n============================================================\nFINDINGS\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with compliance findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2367,"cache_read_input_tokens":34493,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2367},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ffe22035-2715-4aff-ac4b-cff374a0d4eb","uuid":"8b831e45-71a8-49d2-bfe6-83ccf942b1c3","request_id":"req_011Cc2iYPkKrYUiWDoDaSB63"}
